  "response_text": "The commercial opens outside a warmly lit barber shop. A classic red, white, and blue striped barber pole stands large in the foreground, and through the glass storefront a barber chair and salon furnishings are visible. On the window, large curved red letters read “BARBIERI ROSSI.” Inside, an older light-skinned man with short gray hair, thick dark eyebrows, and a white short-sleeved barber-style shirt stands near a seated customer. He turns and gestures toward the front window, as if noticing something there.\n\nA close view of the older man’s face shows him looking serious and slightly wary. He turns his head toward the window. Behind him, the red lettering on the glass blurs into the background. A small animated honeybee mascot appears outside near the reversed window lettering. The bee is golden yellow with big white eyes, long black antennae, tiny translucent wings, an orange shirt, black pants, and oversized white sneakers. He hovers in midair beside a large red letter, smiling and waving, then lifts an arm in an enthusiastic, showy pose.\n\nBack inside, the older barber stands in the warmly lit shop with mirrors, bottles, shelves, and a barber chair around him. He points toward the animated bee and holds something small in his other hand. His expression is alert but curious. The scene then shifts to a breakfast-style product display: a Honey Nut Cheerios box stands upright beside a bowl filled with cereal and a spoon. The orange-brown box clearly reads “Honey Nut Cheerios” and shows the bee mascot and a honey dipper over a pile of ring-shaped cereal. The animated bee lands near the bowl, then pops up and bounces above it, smiling broadly. He poses proudly beside the box, presenting it with one hand as if introducing the cereal.\n\nThe bee gestures with a thumbs-up near the bowl and the Honey Nut Cheerios package. For a moment the barber’s reflection or the shop interior appears faintly behind the product display, suggesting the bee and cereal are being seen through or near the shop window. The bee moves in front of the older man’s image and then reappears standing on top of the cereal in the bowl. He holds up a single larger ring-shaped oat cereal piece, examining it fondly. He presses it close to his face with eyes closed, then lifts it outward with a big open-mouthed smile, as if singing its praises or celebrating it.\n\nThe older barber watches with a softened expression. His face fills the view as he looks sideways, the corners of his mouth tightening into a restrained, amused smirk. He seems to be evaluating the bee’s performance but is no longer stern.\n\nThe bee next clings to the side of a glass honey jar. The jar is filled with amber honey, and the word “HONEY” is etched or printed in large pale letters across the front. The bee hugs the jar with both arms, eyes closed, looking blissful and affectionate. He slides or leans along the smooth glass, still holding on, then suddenly opens his eyes and pulls back in surprise, as if reacting to something off to the side.\n\nThe barber’s face returns, now warmly lit and more amused. He narrows one eye slightly, then smiles with a knowing, pleased look. The focus moves to a younger light-skinned man seated at the barber station. He has short dark hair and is seen from behind and in a mirror. His reflection shows him wearing a light-colored shirt, looking forward with a neutral, slightly puzzled expression. Small photos or postcards are tucked around the mirror frame, adding to the everyday barbershop setting.\n\nOutside the shop, the older barber is now seated on a bench beneath the window, holding a bowl of cereal in one hand and a spoon in the other. The Honey Nut Cheerios box sits on the window ledge to his left, clearly visible. He lifts a spoonful to his mouth and eats. In close view, he pulls the spoon away, chews, closes his eyes briefly, and then smiles with quiet satisfaction. His expression becomes increasingly pleased, almost mischievous,